    "Body": " Conversational Engineer - Research Intern Soul Machines - San Francisco, CA Quick Apply Job Details InternshipEstimated: $36,000 - $49,000 a year7 hours ago Qualifications Web Development Communication Skills Machine Learning JavaScript Python Master's Degree Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description Come and join the super talented team at Soul Machines on our mission to change the face of technology. If you're looking for a company and role that's interesting, can stretch you and put you at the forefront of AI then this could be a great fit for you. As a Conversational Engineer Research Intern, you will be responsible for building the way our Digital People interact and communicate with Soul Machines users. These are not chatbots but character-based experiences expected to be highly conversational, interactive, and emotionally engaging. You will help guide the implementation and development of Digital People across a variety of verticals and use cases. Additionally, you will work with our internal development teams to improve processes, technologies, and research related to state-of-the-art interactions with Soul Machines Digital People. This role is an exciting opportunity to create groundbreaking, autonomous humanoid solutions that redefine organizations, achieve key business outcomes, and pioneer captivating, character experiences for the world's most recognized brands. Key Responsibilities: Bring our Digital People to life by engineering engaging and enjoyable personalities. Design and implement all elements of conversation for our Digital People. Contribute to the development of internal tools for streamlining conversational content development from design to implementation. Explore, create, and optimize intents, utterances, entities, and other conversational signals. Engage in dialog engineering, testing, and training for continuous learning and improvement. Perform failure analysis, custom configuration, QA, and other changes on a per-user and customer basis. Work closely with R&D to create technical specifications for how to improve the conversational creation process. Balance business requirements with technical feasibility requirements to set expectations on new projects. Recommend changes in development, maintenance, and system standards. Influence our conversation engineering process and document methods to support the testing and development of conversational interfaces. Essential skills: Excellent communication skills with an awareness of and ability to optimize interaction experiences. Fundamental programming skills. Experience in one or more of the following languages: Python, JavaScript, Ruby, Java. Experience working with NLU/NLP systems such as IBM Watson Conversation, DialogFlow, Microsoft LUIS, RASA, or more. Collaborative design approach and positive attitude. Hands-on work ethic with the ability to rapidly prototype and adapt to changes in a fast-paced environment. A consumer of new technology with a keen interest to explore emerging trends. Desired skills: Strong interest in AGI and HCI. Web development skills 1+ years' experience with machine learning. BS/MS in Computer/Social Science, Engineering, or related/equivalent field ideally with a significant machine learning or AI component. Understanding of modern conversational AI concepts. Ability to create user flow diagrams and open to learning new UX and conversational design prototyping tools. Experience with interactive storytelling. Experienced working in a start-up (or an agile environment) is a plus. "
